definitions.definition: A peritonsillar abscess ; a painful pus -filled inflammation or abscess of the tonsils and surrounding tissues, usually a complication of tonsillitis , caused by bacterial infection and often accompanied by fever.

main_definition: ( medicine ) A peritonsillar abscess ; a painful pus -filled inflammation or abscess of the tonsils and surrounding tissues, usually a complication of tonsillitis , caused by bacterial infection and often accompanied by fever.
